rounds.response:
To guarantee a win on my next move, I need to set up a double threat: positions where any single follow-up move by me would complete two different three-in-a-row lines, forcing Player 1 to block one while I take the other.

I can create a diagonal 0-4-8 with 0 already blocked, while simultaneously aiming for a horizontal 6-7-8 and vertical 2-5-8. The only spot I must watch is if Player 1 saves [8].

Blocking [8] or [2] will let me win back position 5 or 0 after, so the best spot to threaten both diagonal and horizontal win is 8.
